<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Hi S=
tephen,<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Belo=
w is a copy of an email which I sent to all parties this afternoon outlayin=
g the expected time frames of the results which will be available to be sha=
red with all regarding test results from
 23 Mays Street, Devonport.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p=
>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Prio=
r to receiving the report from the forensic testing =E2=80=93 I am keen to =
take whatever steps I can to progress the claim.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Prel=
iminary results and findings suggest that we may have a relatively complete=
 understanding of what the final scope of works will be to fully remediate =
the property under the claim.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p=
>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-US" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">If w=
e accept on a preliminary basis that the scope of works required to remedia=
te the property is
